  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Tricuspid valve insufficiency (TI) is often noted on echocardiography. Although severe TI is
      known to cause significant morbidity and mortality, no good guidelines are available to guide
      intervention. Literature is mostly confined to tricuspid valve repair concomitant with mitral
      valve repair. Treatment options for isolated repair have not been investigated thoroughly.

      The investigators want to evaluate retrospectively the outcome of isolated tricuspid valve
      repair, performed in our center. By doing this, the investigators want to evaluate predictors
      of outcome after repair.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
